HEADWORD: Rococo
<hw>Ro*co"co</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.; of uncertain
etymology.]</ety> <def>A florid style of ornamentation which prevailed
in Europe in the latter part of the eighteenth century.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rococo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rococo
<hw>Ro*co"co</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the style
called rococo; like rococo; florid; fantastic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

